Message.MsgText: PROX0054W=PROX0054W: Routing Rule {0} will be ignored.
Message.Explanation: All of the required elements of the specified routing rule are not completely defined and cannot be routed to.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure a URI Group, virtual host, and routing action are specified in this routing rule.

Message.MsgText: PROX0064I=PROX0064I: Filters deployed by the proxy are listed below in execution order by protocol and filter point: {0}
Message.Explanation: All of the installed filters are displayed.
Message.UserResponse: None

Message.MsgText: PROX0063W=PROX0063W: A filter named {0} does not exist.
Message.Explanation: Indicates an attempt was made to modify a filter that does not exist.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the filter name was typed correctly. Also, filter names are case sensitive.

Message.MsgText: PROX0069W=PROX0069W: The static routing file directory is not set and static routing is enabled.
Message.Explanation: When static routing is enabled, the static routing file directory must be set to a valid directory that contains the exported static routing XML file.
Message.UserResponse: Review the configuration and set the static file routing directory to a valid directory that contains the exported static routing XML file.

Message.MsgText: PROX0053W=PROX0053W: Problems occurred while creating error logs.
Message.Explanation: No logging will occur due to the unhandled event.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure the specified log file name(s) are valid and accessible.

Message.MsgText: PROX0073I=PROX0073I: HTTP Proxy quiesce completed.
Message.Explanation: The HTTP Proxy quiesce is completed.
Message.UserResponse: None

Message.MsgText: PROX0059E=PROX0059E: Object cache instance {0} is not properly configured for proxy-cache use.
Message.Explanation: The proxy server requires a specific configuration for its object cache. The proxy server cannot start with this condition.
Message.UserResponse: Either disable proxy server caching, or ensure the proxy server object cache is configured to enable NIO support.

Message.MsgText: PROX0068W=PROX0068W: The specified time mapping could not be converted to a valid time object.
Message.Explanation: A value that was not valid was provided that prevented the time mapping from being converted into a valid time.
Message.UserResponse: Review the time mapping configuration and specify a valid time. Hours are represented between 0-23 inclusive and minutes between 0-59 inclusive. For example, 10:30.

Message.MsgText: PROX0052W=PROX0052W: Problems occurred while handling error page application URI. Error Page URI={0}
Message.Explanation: A host for the error page application could not be found.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the error page application URI is located in an available Web module or routing rule.

Message.MsgText: PROX0072I=PROX0072I: HTTP Proxy quiesce started.
Message.Explanation: The HTTP Proxy received a start quiesce request.
Message.UserResponse: None

Message.MsgText: PROX0058W=PROX0058W: The following rewrite rule is improperly formatted and will not be active - FROM URL PATTERN: {0} TO URL PATTERN: {1}
Message.Explanation: Indicates one or both of the supplied URL patterns cannot be parsed
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the patterns do not contain any typos and are formatted according to RFC 2396

Message.MsgText: PROX0062I=PROX0062I: The ordinal of filter: {0} was set to: {1}
Message.Explanation: A filter's ordinal was modified.
Message.UserResponse: None.

Message.MsgText: PROX0061W=PROX0061W: Filter: {0} is internal and cannot be modified.
Message.Explanation: Indicates a user incorrectly attempted to modify an internal filter. Only custom filters can be modified.
Message.UserResponse: None.

Message.MsgText: PROX0067W=PROX0067W: The method {0} was unable to complete successfully due to an argument that is not valid: {1}
Message.Explanation: A value that was not valid was provided that caused the method to fail.
Message.UserResponse: Review mbean command and use correct argument(s).

Message.MsgText: PROX0071I=PROX0071I: HTTP Proxy has informed the load balancer of readiness.
Message.Explanation: The HTTP Proxy is successfully responding to load balancer inquiries.
Message.UserResponse: None

Message.MsgText: PROX0057W=PROX0057W: The URL {0} from is improperly formatted and cannot be parsed.
Message.Explanation: A URL received from a server is not formatted according to RFC 2396.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the format of the specified URL.

Message.MsgText: PROX0051E=PROX0051E: Caught unhandled exception from doFilter in filter={0}; exception={1}.
Message.Explanation: The identified filter failed to handle an event. No error response will be built because the response is already committed.
Message.UserResponse: Review the log file for related reasons as to why the filter failed. If the problem persists, contact the vendor for the filter.

Message.MsgText: PROX0070W=PROX0070W: The static routing file directory does not contain any files and static routing is enabled.
Message.Explanation: When static routing is enabled, the static routing file directory must contain the exported XML routing files or the proxy will fail to route requests.
Message.UserResponse: Review the configuration and ensure the static routing file directory contains one or more XML files generated from the TargetTreeMbean on the Deployment Manager of the target cells.

Message.MsgText: PROX0060I=PROX0060I: The filter {0} has the following filter initialization custom property set: {1} {2}
Message.Explanation: Indicates a filter initialization custom property recognized by the proxy was set.
Message.UserResponse: None.

Message.MsgText: PROX0066I=PROX0066I: No filters are available to be displayed.
Message.Explanation: Indicates no filters are available to be displayed for the specified filter protocol(s) and filter point(s).
Message.UserResponse: None

Message.MsgText: PROX0050E=PROX0050E: Caught unhandled exception from doFilter in filter={0}; exception={1}.
Message.Explanation: The identified filter failed to handle an event. A proxy server internal error response will be built.
Message.UserResponse: Review the log file for related reasons as to why the filter failed. If the problem persists, contact the vendor for the filter.

Message.MsgText: PROX0056I=PROX0056I: The custom property {0} with the value {1} is recognized but not active on the proxy.
Message.Explanation: Indicates that the specified custom property is recognized by the proxy server, but you must restart the proxy server for this value to become active.
Message.UserResponse: Restart the proxy server if you require the custom property value to be operational at this time.

Message.MsgText: PROX0065I=PROX0065I: A subset of the filters deployed by the proxy are listed below in execution order by protocol and filter point: {0}
Message.Explanation: Filters are being displayed based on the protocol and filter point specified.
Message.UserResponse: None

Message.MsgText: PROX0055I=PROX0055I: The custom property {0} with the value {1} is recognized and active on the proxy.
Message.Explanation: Indicates that the specified custom property has been successfully processed by the proxy server.
Message.UserResponse: None.
